Mattijah:
This is pretty pointless in this case.
- `'cache'` and `'serverInfo'` are defined strings not some unknown values provided by the client.
- There is checking of the type anyway.

So for example this

```
if ('cache' in this.options) {
    if (typeof(this.options.cache) === 'number') {
        this.cache = this.options.cache;
    } else if (! this.options.cache) {
        this.cache = false;
    }
 }
```

could be

```
if (typeof this.options.cache === 'number' || this.options.cache === false) {
   this.cache = this.options.cache;
}
```
